        <head>To the most high
	  <lb/>and mighty princesse,
	  <lb/><persName>Mary Henriette,
	  <lb/>q<vuji>v</vuji>een of <placeName>Great 
	    <lb/>Britaine</placeName>,
	  <lb/><placeName>France</placeName> and <placeName>Ireland</placeName>:
	  <lb/>and so<vuji>v</vuji>veraigne lady
	  <lb/>of the iles of the 
	  <lb/><placeName>British Ocean</placeName></persName>.</head>
        <opener>
          <salute rend="first-indent(0)"><hi rend="class(#DIC)">M</hi><hi rend="case(allcaps)">ay</hi> it pleaſe your moſt gracious
	  <lb/>Ma<vuji>i</vuji>eſtie;</salute>
        </opener>
        <p rend="slant(italic)"><hi rend="case(smallcaps)">Being</hi> to publish to the vie<hi rend="slant(upright)">w</hi>
	  <lb/>of the <hi rend="slant(upright)">W</hi>orld, the Life of the Mi­
	  <lb/>rour and Princeſſe of Religious Foundreſſes <persName>S. Cla­
	    <lb/>re</persName>; and being, according to the Cuſtome no leſſe
	  <lb/>frequented than laudable, to bethink our ſel<vuji>u</vuji>es of
	  <lb/>ſome grand Perſonage, <vuji>v</vuji>nder <hi rend="slant(upright)">w</hi>hoſe Protection it
	  <lb/>might paſſe, it ſeemed to <vuji>v</vuji>s impertinent to entertai­
	  <lb/>ne any long Conſult, to that purpoſe, ſeeing your
	  <lb/>Ma<vuji>i</vuji>estie, did at the very firſt deliberation, occurse
	  <lb/>to our thoughts, accompanied with many Titles
	  <lb/>clayming to your matchles Excellencie, the Dedica­
	  <lb/>tory addreſſe and Protection of the <hi rend="slant(upright)">w</hi>orke.  For firſt,
	  <lb/>if <hi rend="slant(upright)">w</hi>eed<gap desc="printed" reason="flawed-reproduction" extent="approx. 1 word"/> the Royall and thrice reno<hi rend="slant(upright)">w</hi>­
<mw rend="align(center)" type="sig">á2</mw>
<mw rend="align(right)break(no)" type="catch">ned</mw>
<pb n="04"/>
<milestone n="á2v" unit="sig"/>
<mw rend="place(fullpagesurround)" type="border">#rule</mw>
	  <lb/>ned Progenie of <placeName rend="slant(upright)">France</placeName>, from <hi rend="slant(upright)">w</hi>hence your Ma­
	  <lb/><vuji>i</vuji>eſtie is extracted, it ſeemeth a thing proper, if not
	  <lb/>hereditary, to that Princely familie, to be addicted to
	  <lb/>the children of our <mcr rend="slant(upright)">Seraphical</mcr> Father, <persName rend="slant(upright)">S. Francis</persName>.
	  <lb/>To whom God communicated <persName>Abraham's</persName> pri<vuji>u</vuji>i­
	  <lb/>ledge (<bibl><regMe>Geneſ. 12.)</regMe></bibl> <quote rend="slant(upright)">I will bleſſe them that
	    <lb/>bleſſe thee and curſe them that curſe thee.</quote> In 
	  <lb/>ſo much, as that great Honour of <placeName rend="slant(upright)">France</placeName>, and
	  <lb/>glory of Kings, <persName>S. Lewis</persName> <hi rend="slant(upright)">w</hi>ho (being by his Mo­
	  <lb/>ther, for her ſingular De<vuji>u</vuji>otion to our holy Father,
	  <lb/>tendred to the <orgName rend="slant(upright)">Freers</orgName> to be educated by them in
	  <lb/>their Monaſtery) ſayd: that yf he could part and 
	  <lb/>di<vuji>u</vuji>ide himſelfe in two, he <hi rend="slant(upright)">w</hi>ould bequeath one part
	  <lb/>of himſelfe to the <orgName rend="slant(upright)">Freers</orgName>: but being he <hi rend="slant(upright)">w</hi>as not able,
	  <lb/>for the important affaires of his Cro<hi rend="slant(upright)">w</hi>ne in ſo ſtrict
	  <lb/>a manner to become a child of our holy Father, he
	  <lb/>made himſelfe a Member of his <orgName>Third Order</orgName>; for
	  <lb/><hi rend="slant(upright)">w</hi>hich reaſon, he hath merited an immortall glory
	  <lb/>in the Roll of the ſaints of that Order. And <unclear reason="flawed-reproduction">indeed,</unclear>
	  <lb/><hi rend="slant(upright)">w</hi>hat your Ma<vuji>i</vuji>eſties De<vuji>u</vuji>otion hath been towards
	  <lb/><persName>S. Francis</persName>, you ha<vuji>u</vuji>e yeelded ſufficient proof and
	  <lb/>teſtimonie <unclear reason="flawed-reproduction">t</unclear>hereof; <hi rend="slant(upright)">w</hi>hen before your comming into
	  <lb/><placeName>England</placeName> (<unclear reason="flawed-reproduction">as <hi rend="slant(upright)">w</hi>e are</unclear> informed) together with your
	  <lb/>Royall Brother <persName>K. Lewis</persName>, now prepotent Monarch
	  <lb/>of <placeName>France</placeName>, you publicly at <placeName>Paris</placeName>, with him, re­
	  <lb/>cei<vuji>u</vuji>ed <persName>S. Francis</persName> <unclear reason="flawed-reproduction">Cord</unclear>, a <hi rend="slant(upright)">Symbole</hi> and <hi rend="slant(upright)">Reco­
	    <lb/>gniſance</hi> of the Sacred Paſſion of our Sou<vuji>u</vuji>eraigne
	  <lb/>Redeemer, for <hi rend="slant(upright)">w</hi>hich this Sodalitie is <unclear reason="flawed-reproduction">enſtiled</unclear> the
	  <lb/><orgName>Arch confraternitie</orgName>, as ha<vuji>u</vuji>ing a more honorable
	  <lb/>Inſtitution and Dedica<unclear reason="flawed-reproduction">t</unclear>ion than any other Confra­
	  <lb/>ternitie <hi rend="slant(upright)">w</hi>hatſoe<vuji>u</vuji>er.  Againe: yf <hi rend="slant(upright)">w</hi>e propoſed to our
	  <lb/>Conſideration, the ſupereminencie of this firſt <mcr>Plant</mcr>
<mw rend="align(right)slant(italic)" type="catch">of</mw>
